# Secret-detection patterns for the commit-msg hook (CODING-STANDARDS.md §15.2).
#
# One extended-regex (grep -E) per line. Blank lines and lines beginning with
# '#' are ignored. Matched against the *added* lines of staged content. A match
# blocks the commit; a genuine false positive is waived with a commit-message
# footer: `kennel-secret-waiver: <reason>`.
#
# Keep patterns specific. The high-entropy hex line at the end is deliberately
# broad and will catch checksums and digests — that is the case the waiver
# footer exists for.

# Private key headers (PEM / OpenSSH / PGP).
-----BEGIN ([A-Z0-9]+ )?PRIVATE KEY-----
-----BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----
-----BEGIN PGP PRIVATE KEY BLOCK-----

# AWS access key id.
\bAKIA[0-9A-Z]{16}\b

# GitHub tokens (classic and fine-grained) and app/refresh tokens.
\bghp_[0-9A-Za-z]{36}\b
\bgithub_pat_[0-9A-Za-z_]{22,}\b
\b(gho|ghu|ghs|ghr)_[0-9A-Za-z]{36}\b

# Slack tokens.
\bxox[baprs]-[0-9A-Za-z-]{10,}\b

# Generic "secret = <long value>" assignments (key/secret/token/password). The
# scan runs case-insensitively, so these keywords match any casing.
(secret|token|password|passwd|api[_-]?key)[[:space:]]*[:=][[:space:]]*['"][^'"]{12,}['"]

# High-entropy hex of plausible secret length (broad; waiver-prone).
\b[0-9a-fA-F]{64,}\b
